17 B. A Except as provided in subsection 7, a retail establishment containing a pharmacy
18 is ineligible for a retail tobacco license. A retail establishment containing a pharmacy
19 that engages in retail sales, including retail sales through vending machines or in free
20 distribution of tobacco products, and sells, to anyone or keeps for sale or gives away
21 in the course of trade any tobacco products to anyone commits a civil violation for
22 which a fine of not more than $2,000 may be adjudged. Each day a retail establishment
