8 SUMMARY
99 This bill creates an exception to the provision of law that prohibits a retail
1100 establishment that contains a pharmacy from obtaining a retail tobacco license. Under the
1111 bill, a grocery store containing a pharmacy is eligible for a retail tobacco license if the store
1122 has no more than 26,000 square feet of customer-accessible sales area; the pharmacy was
1133 established in the grocery store prior to July 7, 2025 and is independently licensed and
1144 operates in a separately demised, leased space; all tobacco sales are made from the grocery
1155 store's independent inventory and point-of-sale system; and the grocery store complies with
1166 all other requirements under the provisions governing retail tobacco licenses.
17 The bill also removes references to the sale of tobacco through vending machines or
18 the practice of giving away tobacco products in the course of trade, both of which were
19 made illegal by Public Law 2025, chapter 367.
